British preparatory committee formed 
  &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, September 22 (KCNA) -- A British preparatory committee for celebrating the 54th anniversary of the founding of the Worker's Party of Korea was formed in London on September 11. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
    Keith Bennett, chairman of the Korea Friendship and Solidarity Campaign of Britain, was elected chairman of the committee.

Solidarity meeting of Korean and Japanese women
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;  Pyongyang, September 22 (KCNA) -- A solidarity meeting of Korean and Japanese women was held here yesterday. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   Present at the meeting were the delegation of the Japanese Women's Liaison Council for Solidarity with the Korean Women and working women in Pyongyang. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   In her speech, Ri Chong Il, chairwoman of the Korean Women's Society for Solidarity with the Asian Women, said that Korean people know well about the just activities conducted by the Japanese Women's Liaison Council for the Peace and Reunification of Korea and the genuine improvement of the relations between the DPRK and Japan. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   She noted that the council's expression of full support to the DPRK government's statement issued in last August was a manifestation of the principled stand of the Japanese women to be guided by justice and conscience and make Japan fulfil its responsibility and role as part of the international community. She urged the Japanese authorities to roll back immediately their policy to stifle the DPRK which may lead to its self-destruction and make an honest apology and adequate compensation for the crimes Japan committed against the Korean people in the past. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   Speaking next, head of the delegation and a representative of the liaison council Sumiko Shimizu, deputy leader of the Social Democratic Party of Japan and a member of the House of Councilors, declared that Japan has to liquidate the past crimes if good neighborly relations are to be opened between the DPRK and Japan.  She expressed her support to the DPRK government statement issued in August. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   She said that the issue of "comfort women for the army" is a crime against the dignity of women and the responsibility for its solution rests with the Japanese government. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The Japanese government is obliged to mend its wrongdoings in a responsible manner, she said, noting that if the Japanese government values its prestige and moral principle, it should resume the talks for the normalization of the relations with the DPRK and make every effort to make them fruitful and, at the same time, improve the legal status of  the Korean residents in Japan and guarantee  democratic national rights to them at an early date. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  She called upon the women of the two countries to firmly solidarize with each other to hasten the establishment of the good neighborly relations between the two countries and undertake a joint struggle for the Korean reunification and the peace in northeast Asia. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The meeting was also addressed by women of the two countries. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   A resolution was adopted at the meeting to undertake a more dynamic solidarity movement demanding the Japanese authorities roll back their hostile policy towards the DPRK and make an apology and compensation for the liquidation of the crimes committed by the Japanese imperialists in the period of their colonial rule over Korea.

Agreement on news exchange signed between DPRK and Iran
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;  Pyongyang, September 22 (KCNA) -- The Central News Agency of the Democratic People's Republic of Korea (KCNA) and the Islamic Republic News Agency of Iran (IRNA) signed an agreement on exchange and cooperation in news service in Teheran on Sept. 19. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
It was signed by KCNA director general Kim Tok Yong and his IRNA counterpart Fereydoun Verdinejad.

KCNA on bellicose utterances of colonial stooge
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, September 22 (KCNA) -- Jo Song Thae, "Minister of Defense" of South Korea, said at a "seminar" on Sept. 17 that now it is necessary to increase defence power to serve the double purpose of independently coping with the threat from the north and change of security situation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   Shamelessly distorting the provocative incident at the west sea in which South Korea suffered a bitter defeat, he argued that strong defense posture taken in advance can frustrate any provocation of the enemy in emergency. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   Such utterances of Jo Song Thae revealed once again his true colors as a colonial stooge of the U.S. and clearly proved that the policy towards the north of the self-proclaimed "people's government" is an anti-north confrontation policy and the policy for a war against the north from A to Z. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
It is ridiculous of the "ROK army," a colonial mercenary of the U.S., to "independently cope with something." &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   It is nothing but a stooge's servile pledge to supply all the cannon fodder needed for the U.S. war of aggression to dominate Asia as well as  Korea in its strategical interests by increasing military spending to be covered with taxes collected from the South Korean people.   &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 As long as such flunkeyist quislings as Jo Song Thae are hell-bent on the anti-north confrontation and war maneuvers serving the master's interests, it is quite impossible to bring detente to the Korean peninsula and improve inter-Korean relations. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   Countless are grave crimes committed by jo song thae against the nation since he became "Minister of Defense."&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   Anti-north confrontation fanatics and warmongers like him must be liquidated at an early date to hasten reconciliation and great unity of the nation and independent and peaceful reunification of the country.

Death anniversary of Kim Jong Suk
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, September 22 (KCNA) -- The economic and trade councilors corps, embassy officials in charge of cultural and friendly relations and women of foreign embassies and missions of international organizations in Korea laid wreaths and observed a moment's silence before the bust of the great communist revolutionary fighter Kim Jong Suk at the Revolutionary Martyrs' Cemetery on Mt. Taesong on September 21 on the occasion of the 50th anniversary of her death. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The embassy officials visited the Revolutionary Museum of the Ministry of Railways and heard about the revolutionary exploits of Kim Jong Suk. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   Meanwhile, a film show was held at the Pyongyang Koryo Hotel for women of foreign embassies and missions of international organizations here. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The participants saw Korean documentary film "the Great Communist Revolutionary Fighter Comrade Kim Jong Suk, Woman Commander of Mt. Paektu" part two.

Letter to Kim Jong Il from Ri In Mo
  &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;  Pyongyang, September 22 (KCNA) - General Secretary  Kim Jong Il Tuesday received a letter from Ri In Mo, the incarnation of faith and will, on the occasion of the 50th death anniversary of the communist revolutionary fighter Kim Jong Suk. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
An anti-Japanese woman commander, she set out in the sacred war for the liberation of the country in her early years. She was the great sunray of the nation who brought about the nation's revival through a bloody struggle under the guidance of the President Kim Il Sung, he noted, and went on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  She was the praiseworthy incarnation of benevolence and the great mother who put her heart and soul into the building of a new country and the reunification of the nation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   On Mt. Paektu, a sacred ancestral mountain, she brought up the sun of guidance who would illumine the world in the 21st century and provided guarantee for the continuation of Juche revolution. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The prosperity and strong independence of Kim Il Sung's nation are associated with her precious blood and sweat and her sublime image is cherished deep in the minds of the Korean people as a permanent portrait, he wrote.

Letter to Kim Jong Il from NDFSK
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, September 22 (KCNA) -- General Secretary  Kim Jong Il today received a letter from the central committee of the National Democratic Front of South Korea (NDFSK) on the occasion of the 50th death anniversary of the communist revolutionary fighter Kim Jong Suk. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The letter noted that Kim Jong Suk performed immortal feats by devoting her all to the realization of the revolutionary cause of the President Kim Il Sung with a clear outlook on the leader, holding him in high esteem in the years of the struggle for the country's liberation and building of a new state. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   Noting that she provided the cause of Juche with enduring vitality by giving birth to a son of guerrillas, the future sun, and bringing him up at dawn of the country's liberation, the letter praised this as a great exploit which will shine brightly forever. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The letter went on to say: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   True to the will of Kim Jong Suk in her lifetime, you held President Kim Il Sung in high esteem as the eternal sun of Juche and defended his idea and cause. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 
   It is the priceless fruition of your leadership that the north has emerged as a political and ideological power and a military power of the times pervaded with the spirit of devotedly defending the leader and the spirit of human bombs, and the whole country and all the people are performing world-startling feats by dashing forward to build an economic power. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The letter renewed the determination of the National Democratic Front of South Korea to learn from Kim Jong Suk, supreme incarnation of devoted defender of the leader and build up its organization as a death-defying corps and the rank of loyalists unshaken in any adversity.

Letter to Kim Jong Il from O Ik Je
 &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, September 22 (KCNA) -- General Secretary  Kim Jong Il on September 21 received a letter from O Ik Je, vice-chairman of the Committee for the Peaceful Reunification of the Fatherland, who defected to the north from South Korea, on the occasion of the 50th anniversary of the death of Kim Jong Suk, a communist revolutionary fighter. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The letter said: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The life of Kim Jong Suk is a model of life that taught the genuine value of life in practice, not with theory. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   History has seen no heroines but Kim Jong Suk, woman guerrilla commander who took a rifle in her hand with her infinite love for the country and people in her early years and broke through all difficulties and ordeals for a long time for the liberation of the country. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The highest loyalty and filial piety of Kim Jong Il helped hold Kim Jong Suk in high esteem as the eternal mother of the homeland of Juche as it did hold the great Kim Il Sung in high esteem as the eternal President. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   It also created a new world of loyalty and filial piety in this land and brought up all people in the north as loyal and dutiful subjects.

Brilliant life of Kim Jong Suk
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;  Pyongyang, September 22 (KCNA) -- Today is the 50th death anniversary of indomitable communist revolutionary fighter and anti-Japanese heroine Kim Jong Suk (September 22, 1949). &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   On this day working people from different parts of the country are visiting her native home and revolutionary sites and retrospecting her brilliant life in profound veneration. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   On December 24, 1917, she was born into a patriotic and revolutionary family in Hoeryong town, Hoeryong county,  North Hamgyong Province. As her parents and her brothers were killed by Japanese imperialists when she was little, she took part in the sacred war to liberate the country in her teens. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   She joined the Korean People's Revolutionary Army commanded by the President Kim Il Sung in September, 1935, and displayed unrivalled bravery and self-sacrificing spirit in many battles. Moving stories about Kim Jong Suk who earned fame as a crack shot in every fierce battle were related as a legend among people and guerrillas. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   She was an able and experienced political underground worker. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   She organized new grass roots-level organizations of the party and conducted an energetic work to expand and develop the network of the association for the restoration of the fatherland despite the enemy's cordon, to implement the strategic plan of the President. She thus aroused the people to the anti-Japanese war and contributed to laying the organizational and ideological foundation for the founding of the party. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   She was a model of staunch lifeguards who defended the headquarters of the revolution politically and  ideologically with her life in the whole period of the anti-Japanese revolutionary struggle. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   After the liberation of the country she rendered great services to build a new country and realize the women's emancipation and develop their movement upholding the noble intention of President Kim Il Sung. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
Factories and farms in North Hamgyong Province, South Phyongan Province and Pyongyang city, the building site of Kim Il Sung University, the sites of the Pothong River improvement work, film studio and Samhung Middle School, the Pyongyang Institute and the Security Officers Training Center and many other parts of the country were associated with  her immortal exploits performed for the building of a rich and powerful sovereign and independent state. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   Her statues, bust and historic monuments were erected in revolutionary sites of the country including her native home in Hoeryong and the Revolutionary Martyrs' Cemetery on Mt. Taesong in order to hand down through generations her great contribution to the cause of the country's liberation and her total dedication to the building of a new country. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   And many places and units were named after her.

Kim Jong Suk's passing away commemorated 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, September 22 (KCNA) -- Various events took place on the occasion of the 50th anniversary of the passing away of Kim Jong Suk. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   A remember-Kim Jong Suk stage of trade union members entitled "Eternal smile of mother" was held at the Central Workers Hall on Tuesday. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The speakers stressed that the greatest revolutionary feat of Kim Jong Suk is that she gave steadfast continuity to the revolutionary cause of Juche started by the  President Kim Il Sung. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   A remember-Kim Jong Suk meeting of agricultural workers entitled "Anti-Japanese heroine Kim Jong Suk will always be with red flag" and a stage of young vanguard "memorial evening to remember mother" were held at the Central Youth Hall on the same day. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   Agricultural workers recollected Kim Jong Suk who set out on the road of the revolutionary struggle in her early years and devoted her all to the anti-Japanese revolutionary struggle and the struggle to build a new country. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   On the stage of young vanguard the performers loudly sang of the firm resolution of the young vanguard to devotedly defend the respected Marshal Kim Jong Il, the center of unity and the center of leadership of the Korean revolution, and remain loyal to his idea and leadership, bearing deep in mind the noble revolutionary spirit of Kim Jong Suk. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   An oath-taking meeting of women's union members took place before the statue of Kim Jong Suk in Hoeryong city at the northern tip of Korea on September 21. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   They vowed to learn from her noble example and thoroughly prepare themselves to be true loyal subjects and dutiful daughters who are holding Kim Jong Il in high esteem with loyalty. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   On September 20, a remember-Kim Jong Suk evening entitled "Mother's bright smile is eternal" was held at the April 25 House of Culture and a remember-Kim Jong Suk national fine art exhibition was open at the Korean Art Gallery.

Kim Jong Suk provides continuity to vitality of Korean revolution
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, September 22 (KCNA) -- The Korean people are looking back with deep emotions upon the immortal feats performed by Kim Jong Suk on the occasion of the 50th anniversary of her passing away. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The most brilliant feat performed by her in accomplishing the revolutionary cause of Juche is that she provided a steadfast continuity to the vitality of the Korean revolution. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   Papers here today emphasize this in articles on her immortal revolutionary life and feats. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   Rodong Sinmun says she brought up the sun of communist future, provided a steady continuity to the leadership over the revolutionary cause of Juche pioneered by the President Kim Il Sung and gave the Korean people the greatest glory and happiness of being blessed with the sagacious leader down through generations. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The great fortune of the nation who is blessed with the sagacious leader and commander generation after generation is unthinkable without the warm love and tireless efforts of Kim Jong Suk, the mother of revolution, who brought up the future of Korea and upheld the great sun of the 21st century, the paper notes. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   Minju Joson says: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   It was a great event of our fellow countrymen and a historic event in laying a firm foundation for carrying forward the Korean revolution that Kim Jong Suk gave birth to the respected Kim Jong Il as the great son of the sun's nation amidst the blessings of the era and history. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   She worked heart and soul to bring up Kim Jong Il as the great revolutionary who will faithfully carry forward the revolutionary cause of Juche started by Kim Il Sung.

DPRK founding anniversary celebrated abroad
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;   Pyongyang, September 22 (KCNA) -- The 51st anniversary of the founding of the DPRK was grandly celebrated in different countries. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   General Secretary Kim Jong Il received messages of greetings from more than 120 party leaders of over 60 foreign countries including the general secretary of the central committee of the Communist Party of China and the first secretary of the c.c., the Communist Party of Cuba hoping that the DPRK will be more powerful and prosperous under his wise leadership. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   Floral baskets and bouquets addressed to him were sent to DPRK embassies by the King of Cambodia, the President of Palestine, the leader of Libya, the President and the Prime Minister of Guinea, the president of the People's Council and the Prime Minister of Syria and the Mexican Foreign Minister and other heads of state and high-level figures of political and social circles, political parties and social organizations and international and regional organizations. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   Colorful celebrations including meetings, lecture meetings, photo exhibitions, film shows and receptions were held with large attendance in more than 40 countries. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   A symposium on the Juche idea for independence, peace and friendship in Latin America in the 21st century was held at Guayaquil University of Ecuador. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   Meanwhile, mass media of different countries highly praised the immortal exploits of Kim Jong Il who is further glorifying socialist Korea and widely introduced the superior socialist system of Korea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
Foreign figures and poets including Victor Kulikov, advisor to the Ministry of Defence of Russia, and Candelaria Rodriguez, a woman lawyer of Cuba, published articles speaking highly of the unique method of political administration of Kim Jong Il and national power of Korea.

Kim Jong Suk assisted President in his leadership
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, September 22 (KCNA) -- Today is the 50th death anniversary of Kim Jong Suk (Sept. 22, 1949). &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   Her revolutionary life is one of the great revolutionary and the ardent patriot and loyalist, who started the revolution and adorned the road of revolution with patriotism under the red flag held aloft by the President Kim Il Sung. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   She was a brilliant model of the true loyalist and patriot in assisting the President in steering the work to build a prosperous country. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   She returned in triumph after liberating the country in August, 1945 and visited factories and enterprises, refusing to call at her hometown which was within hail. And she acquainted herself in detail with the reconstruction of factories and encouraged workers in their reconstruction work. One day, she visited a fishing village to go out to sea aboard a boat together with fishermen, and considered measures to stabilize the people's livelihood. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   She went to a village on the outskirts of Pyongyang to get familiar with the peasants' living conditions in January, Juche 35 (1946) where she paid a deep attention to the problem of pencil for pupils. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   As a result, a historic measure was taken to place the problem of pencil as the first agenda item to be taken up by the first meeting of the provisional people's committee of North Korea in February, 1946. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   She conducted energetic activities, giving on-the-site guidance to hundreds of units across the country to successfully carry out the President's line on the building of the party, government and army till her last moment since the liberation of the country. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   Immensely great are the exploits Kim Jong Suk performed by energetically assisting the great President in steering the work for the development and prosperity of the country.

National memorial service on anniv. of Kim Jong Suk's passing away
   &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, September 22 (KCNA) -- Today is the 50th anniversary of the passing away of Kim Jong Suk. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
On this occasion, a national memorial service took place at the April 25 House of Culture in Pyongyang with attendance of Kim Yong Nam, Jo Myong Rok  and other senior party and state officials, anti-Japanese revolutionary fighters working people from all walks of life and people's army soldiers. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The participants observed a moment's silence in memory of Kim Jong Suk. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   A memorial address was made by Yang Hyong Sop, alternate member of the political bureau of the Central Committee of the Worker's Party of Korea and vice-President of the presidium of the Supreme People's Assembly. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   He said: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   Kim Jong Suk devoted 20 years in her 32-year-long life to the revolution. Her life was a noble and brilliant life of the most devoted loyalist to the leader, the greatest mother of revolution and the most ardent patriot of the nation in human history. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;   
   She was born into a patriotic family in Hoeryong, North Hamgyong Province, on December 24, Juche 6 (1917). In hearty response to the President Kim Il Sung's line of liberating the country, she joined the Korean People's Revolutionary Army in September 1935, conducted political and military activities while fighting bloody battles against Japan for ten years and devoted her all to the building of a new country after liberation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   She was a brilliant paragon of loyalists who held high the banner of devotedly defending the leader in the van with absolute worship for President Kim Il Sung. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   During the anti-Japanese armed struggle she firmly safeguarded the headquarters of the revolution in many battles at the risk of her life. She uncovered and shattered the enemy's heinous moves to do harm to the headquarters of the revolution with a high degree of revolutionary vigilance and keen penetration, thus setting a brilliant example as a lifeguard. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   There are many anecdotes about her loyalty in protecting the President from danger during the anti-Japanese struggle and the building of the country. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   She was an unquestioned advocate and a most faithful implementor of the revolutionary idea and line of the leader and an outstanding political activist possessed of distinguished organizational ability and seasoned leadership art. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   She was not only a communist revolutionary fighter endowed with the quality and traits as an outstanding political figure but a peerlessly great woman commander and a legendary heroine produced by the Korean nation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   Her life was the noblest revolutionary life replete with the finest virtues based on the ardent love for the revolutionary comrades and strong affection  for the people. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   Her revolutionary life is throwing more brilliant rays on behalf of the era and history as she brought up the respected Kim Jong Il as the lodestar of Juche and gave steadfast continuity to the Korean revolution, the human cause of independence. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The Korean people should always extend most profound thanks and tribute to her immortal feats as she brought up Kim Jong Il as another leader, the sun of revolution, and thus enabled Kim Il Sung's nation to be blessed with the sagacious leader and commander down through generations. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
The whole party, the entire army and all the people should become human bombs like Ri Su Bok and be ready to die in suicidal explosion like Kil Yong Jo to devoutly defend  the great Kim Jong Il and make every effort for his safety and long life in good health under the uplifted banner of devotedly defending the leader, which is associated with her life and dyed with the blood of the forerunners of the revolution.

Hong Song Nam meets foreigners
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, September 22 (KCNA) -- Hong Song Nam, premier of the cabinet of DPRK,  met and had talks at the Mansudae Assembly Hall today with the delegations and representatives from different countries and the delegation of the Federation of Korean Credit Associations in Japan that had participated in celebrations of the 40th anniversary of the establishment of the Foreign Trade Bank. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
Present there were officials concerned including the president of the Foreign Trade Bank, Kim Jun Chol.
